  43.4.12 ESMF_TimeIsLeapYear - Determine if a Time is in a leap year

   INTERFACE:
       function ESMF_TimeIsLeapYear(time, rc)

   RETURN VALUE:
       logical :: ESMF_TimeIsLeapYear

   ARGUMENTS:
       type(ESMF_Time), intent(in)            :: time
 -- The following arguments require argument keyword syntax (e.g. rc=rc). --
       integer,         intent(out), optional :: rc

   STATUS:
     * This interface is backward compatible with ESMF versions starting
       at 5.2.0r. If code using this interface compiles with any version
       of ESMF starting with 5.2.0r, then it will compile with the current
       version.

   DESCRIPTION:

   Returns .true. if given time is in a leap year, and .false. otherwise.
   See also ESMF_CalendarIsLeapYear().

   The arguments are:

   time
          The ESMF_Time to check for leap year.

   [rc]
          Return code; equals ESMF_SUCCESS if there are no errors.

